      <title>Emacs Running Python on Remote Server</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/20250205125638-emacs_running_python_on_remote_server/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 25 Feb 2025 11:33:00 -0500</pubDate>
      <author>guilhermesalome@gmail.com (Guilherme Salome)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/20250205125638-emacs_running_python_on_remote_server/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Create an executable that will run the code necessary to start Python in the remote server. My script is named &lt;code&gt;remote-python&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;#!/usr/bin/env bash
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;ssh hpclogin -t &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;module load python/3.12; python &lt;/span&gt;$@&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# You could also change the working directory and load a virtual environment:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# ssh hpclogin -t &amp;#34;module load python/3.12; cd ~/Guilherme/CRON/aims-test/; source pyenv/bin/activate; python $@&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Make the script executable:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;chmod +x remote-python
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Modify how Emacs launches the Python interpreter:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
